WHY THESE DATASETS?

I selected datasets based on:
1. Size (need hundreds of thousands of samples)
2. Features (need 20-50 meaningful columns)
3. Recency (2024-2026 datasets preferred)
4. Financial relevance (pre-existing bank/payment indicators)

DATASET 1: PhiUSIIL
- Source: UCI Machine Learning Repository
- Original size: 235,795 rows, 54 features
- Why chosen: Has 'Bank', 'Pay', 'Crypto' features pre-extracted
- Link: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/967

DATASET 2: StealthPhisher
- Source: IEEE DataPort
- Original size: 336,749 rows, 64 features
- Why chosen: Has 'HasBankingKey', 'HasPaymentKey', 'HasCryptoKey'
- Large sample size

DATASET 3: LegitPhish
- Source: Mendeley Data
- Original size: 101,219 rows, 17 features
- Why chosen: Good overlap with PhiUSIIL features

DATASET 4: Malicious URLs
- Source: Kaggle
- Original size: 651,191 rows, 2 columns
- Why chosen: Raw URLs for scale demonstration (reserved for future work)
